stimulusHtml: Which of the following best describes the behavior of the code segment?

features.html:
Consider the following code segment.

 

int[][] arr = {{10, -7, 19, 14},
               {-3, -2, -6, 11},
               {-9, 12, 10, -1}};
int ans = 1;
for (int[] row : arr)
{
   for (int value : row)
   {
      if (value > 0)
      {
         ans = ans * value;
      }
   }
}
System.out.println(ans);

choicesHtml: It prints the product of all the elements in arr.
It prints the product of all the negative elements in arr.
It prints the product of all the positive elements in arr.
It prints nothing because of a run-time error.
